column5: Looking for a last feed at the cottage. Having trouble finding them this fall. Some guys say go deep. Others say shallow on shore at night.  Anybody on them lately?
A buddy does well on Stony every fall at this time in 50 plus FOW. Vertical jigging an ice fishing jigging rapala....tipped with a chunk of worm for meat. If I was out after eyes I'd be looking deep.
As of last weekend they hadn't come into shore at my spots yet. I'll be back out there Saturday night and/or Sunday night to have at 'er again.
Anybody have a recent water temperature up there?
Cameron Lake was 19 this past Monday after being 21  last Friday, it is  dropping every night.
Oh by the way, no walleye caught but Muskies were on fire.
Anybody have a recent water temperature up there?    62.5 to 64 degrees Chris,

66 F here on north Pigeon. Caught 4 eyes this evening all under slot. Bottom bouncing  a crankbait around humps in 20-40 ft. Marked fish in 30-40 ft. Dropshot on them.  Smoke Slammer. 80% bluegills. Rest smaller smallies. Chicken tonight. ?

wallys been biting good other than a couple days with stormy weather cold front stuff. mud to rock areas in the 15-18 ft depths been producing good during day, been getting good numbers buried in thick weeds as well 8 ft. pick your poisen jig grub drop shot cranks harnesses all producing
